# WICHTIG

Damit die Fragen-Datei funktioniert, muss dein Python-Code diese Zeilen enthalten:

```python
import json
import random

@st.cache_data

def load_questions():
    with open("questions.json", "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        data = json.load(f)

    random.shuffle(data)
    return data

if "bank" not in st.session_state:
    st.session_state.bank = load_questions()
```

Und deine Fragenauswahl muss so aussehen:

```python
if st.session_state.q is None:

    remaining = [
        q for q in st.session_state.bank
        if q not in st.session_state.used_questions
    ]

    if len(remaining) == 0:
        st.success("Alle Fragen gespielt!")
        st.stop()

    st.session_state.q = random.choice(remaining)
    st.session_state.used_questions.append(st.session_state.q)
```
